reviews.review_text: I had a fantastic experience at TEC-HUT . The staff here are not only experts in their field but also extremely friendly and helpful. They were able to quickly diagnose and repair my mobile phone as well as laptop, saving me from a lot of inconvenience.
Barry is always so helpful to just go out his way to help me evertime Im there and have seen him do the same for others you have a great employees in barry

A nice little neighborhood outdoor mall with Independent Grocer, a BC Liquor Store, a Starbucks, Kins Market, and an A&W as the larger outlets.  I like how it serves mostly the residential areas around it so it never gets crazy busy but is lively and busy enough to support a variety of stores.  Theres also a public library and professional (health care) office in the same plaza.
Nice place to sit down if youre getting your shopping done. Has a bakery and best priced chinese takeout .

Love this spot for the Independent Market and Kins Produce store. Both have great selection and Kins has the best produce prices. Theres also a couple of fast food restaurants, a liquor store, Starbucks, pharmacy, and more.

I love   Subway! Definitely my first choice. Rarely is there a lineup. I like the fact that its a healthier option. Makes me feel better than eating a greasy fatty burger. They have so many of choices. Beef, sandwich meat, chicken etc... Even plenty of bread choices. I would like a bread with more garlic and cheese in it though. Now toasted or untrusted, double cheese and some of them know how to cut the bread the old way making the well cut instead of the flat cut. Less food falls out I find. Next come the toppings. I can have as much or as little as I want. Oh guess what? Extra toppings are FREE!! YOU tell the maker what YOU want! The maker waits for YOU to decide and doesnt take issue with waiting and makes sure you are satisfied with the end result. I sometimes even have them cut my 6 into 4 because I cant eat a lot in one sitting. They make sure there enough napkins utensils like a spoon for soup. YOU have the choice to dine in or take out. Ive always been able to find a seat. I like that I am taken care of and its all about what I want for once, Im listened to and I can indulge if I want and have that cookie in the end.
Going here for years. Great bakery and Chinese food takeout. Close to liquor store.

Great little neighborhood square with everything you need. The Independent is my go-to grocery store and the staff and service are always good. There s enough variety at Champlain to be your 1 stop shop (Starbucks, Bonnie s Bakery, BC liquor, dollar store, Kins, PURE nails to name a few. And parking is free! You really can t go wrong here.
A great neighbourhood plaza with an Independent grocer, Shoppers Drug Mart, Starbucks and A&W. Inside the food court is a fantastic bakery offering western and eastern style pastries and baked goods!
It s close to my home.  Good to go for groceries, my vet, library, bank, hair salon and last but not least the Starbucks.

Its a small but with everything you need mall. Theres the BCLS, grocery store, Starbucks, dentist, dollar store, a few stores which sell breakfast, lunch and dinner and many other stores which are good to pick anything you need. When the weather is clear and sunny there wont be enough room at the parking lot which makes more convenient to go shopping by bus or park the car somewhere nearby. Good place to go and the prices are not that high, I recommend it.

This plaza has everything - fast food restaurants (burger, pizza, Chinese, etc), produce stores, bakery, bank, library, liquor store, etc. It can get very busy in the weekend or early evenings. Parking can be difficult during that time; just need to wait patiently to get the parking spot.
Nice Street Mall. Attended a training at VPL. Transit accessible from Vancouver West Side.

Great one stop shop. The smokery and bakery is awesome! The independent grocer stocks superstore brand goods (president choice), restaurants, dollar store etc. All in all a great local place to avoid the bustle of the big malls.
Very convenient array of stores. Kind of like a One-Stop shop.

This place is one stop shop!  Youve got the independent grocers which is like a superstore.  If you want some different kind of fresh produce, theres a Kins Market in the complex.  Want a bite to eat after shopping?  You have a choice of Starbucks pastries, delicious onions rings and maybe a beyond meat burger at a&w or maybe some HK style cafe food.  Its all there.  Maybe after that you need to relax and let the food settle .. theres a library there too!

This plaza is great. They basically have almost anything you would need or desire. There are places to eat, a nail salon, liquor store, grocery store and market, bmo, Shoppers,  bakery...and several other things. The only thing missing is a laundromat.

Champlain Mall is great. Ire been coming here since I was 16 years old and it is still  as good as the first time I went tree wit my parents. It is busy and the few stores in the mall offer good value for your money. The surrounding shops are also busy and offer great products.

Good looking small place. We go to this market, mostly when we are visiting our amily doctor. He is the best doctor in town (actually in LMD) ;) This is a place where you can buy insurance, veggies and fruits, or order food for eating in or out. It has different tastes stores, fir different budgets. What we like the most in here, is buying from the grocery store, the French bread. There is no other French bread that has that consistency and tastes as european as the one we buy from here. Its best for spreads or just a simple toast with soup. I always buy triple quantity and keep the extra in the freezer. As any other place in Vancouver, parking is not easy, as there seemed to be less than needed parking spots.
